1 NOTE {geni:about_me} I was born in Hong Kong and lived there for 5 years, and from that point Chinese and Hong Kong culture was influenced me in my travels, hobbies and way of life. We moved to the San Francisco Bay Area (Mill Valley) 
2 CONC and lived there for around 10 years, then moved to Paris for around 4 years, where I finished my french high school studies with the Bacalaureat. In 2004 I wanted to return to sunny and relaxing California for University, which is
2 CONC  where i'm currently at, studying Industrial design with an environmental friendly point of view. I went to Shanghai in 2006 for one year of chinese studies, that's where I had some of the best times of my life. 
