1 NOTE {geni:about_me} https://www.angelfire.com/realm/gotha/gotha/praslin.html
2 CONT
2 CONT 4h) Mathilde Joséphine (1805/6-Oct 1867); m.Pr Sergei Danilovich Kudatschev (d.1862)
2 CONT
2 CONT
2 CONT
2 CONT Countess Mathilde Choiseul-Gouffier, married to Sergei Danilovitch Koudachev was the daughter of Count Octave Choiseull-Gouffier and Victoria Stanislavovna, nee Countess Potocki and granddaughter of Count Gabrie Choiseul-Gouffier,
2 CONC  Ambassador of France to Turkey. He took refuge to the court of Catherine the Great to escape the French Revolution and raised his family in Russia at the imperial court.
2 CONT
2 CONT Countess Mathilde Choiseul-Gouffier was born in Russia, her father Count Octave was the eldest son of Count Marie-Gabriel~Florent-August Choiseul-Gouffier who came from a long line of French nobility which had played important rol
2 CONC es in French history. At the time of the French Revolution he was Ambassador of France in Turkey and took refuge at the court of Katherine the Great and became her counselor. ( see chapter Choiseul~Gouffier). His son founded the R
2 CONC ussian branch of the family and married countess Victoria Potocki, whose father count Felix~Stanislas Potocki had also sought refuge at the court of Katherine after the second partition of Poland. Their daughter Mathilde married P
2 CONC rince Sergei Danilovitch Kudashev. They had 10 children, one of them being my great-great grandfather Vladimir.
