2 CONT He fought in the war against Napoleon in 1812, participated in the battle of Leipzig, Dresden and Ulm and received the order of St. Anna., 3rd degree.
2 CONT
2 CONT He was governor of Kiev
2 CONT
2 CONT He owned important estates in Cherson.
2 CONT
2 CONT He is burried in front of the Krestosdvijenski Church in the Lavra-Pecherskaia which he donated to the monastery. He married Countess Mathilde Choiseul-Gouffier and had 10 children. His grave exists still today in the Lavra with a
2 CONC n inscription from his wife and another one from his children. The monks of the Lavra have taken care of this monument. He is said to have left a lot of money and property to the Lavra. I was told in 1996 that the monks were writi
2 CONC ng a book on him
