1 NOTE {geni:about_me} Demidov, Elisaveta Fedorovna,  born Trepov (27.IX.1885+1978).  Second wife of Pavel Aleksandrovich Demidov.  Left Russia after the revolution and settled in France.  Died in Nice.
2 CONT
2 CONT Demidov, Pavel Aleksandrovich (3.XII.1869+24.VI.1935).  Educated in the Nikolaevski Cadet Corps ,  enterred the Chevalier Gardes Regiment as a "Volunteer" (1890)  and promoted to Cornet in the Regiment two months later (19.XI.1890
2 CONC ),  transferred to the Guard Cavalry Reserve (1894),  Marshal of the nobility of Kremenets (1896-1901),  appointed Official of the 5th Class in the Ministry of the Interior (1902),  Gentleman of the Court (1903),  took part in the
2 CONC  Russo~Japanese War (1904~1905),  went to the Front with the Grand Duke Boris Aleksandrovich with the rank of Staff Captain of Trans~Baikal Cossack Forcs (1904),  appointed adjutant of Grand Duke Boris Aleksandrovich (1905),  Mars
2 CONC hal of the Nobility of the Volynski Government (1907),  Equerry,  Grand Marshal of the Nobility of the Volynski Government.  Left Russia after the revolution and died in Nice. 
