1 NOTE {geni:about_me} Tatiana was the stronger of the sisters, who found her calling in being a diplomate's wife. She followed her husband to postings in Hungary, Germany, Belgium, Ethiopia and Moscow. She finally was able to live in he
2 CONC r "homeland" from which she had to flee with her parents in 1918. She visited her grandparents house in St. Petersburg and her mother's flat there where she had played as a little girl, she bought every Russian antique of which sh
2 CONC e could get hold of  and her apartment in Rome looked like a Russian museum. She  discovered important family documents from the archives in Russia as well as old books mentioning her ancestor Prince Nikolai Danilovitch Koudacheff
2 CONC  and his campaign against Napoleon in 1813. She transferred all her love to animals and cats and dogs were her constant friends at home and were treated as "humans" .
