2 CONT Dimitri was raised in Russia, Harbin (Manchuria) where his father was head of the Chinese Eastern Railroad, and Peking, where his family emigrated after the Russian Revolution and Civil War. He attended the Sorbonne in Paris and r
2 CONC eceived degrees in Electrical and Mechanical engineering. Upon his return to China, he was employed by British General Electric and lived in Tiensin. He emigrated to Canada with his family in 1948 and has resided in the Vancouver 
2 CONC area. He pursued a number of careers in engineering and other fields including Assistant Chief Electrical Engineer on Kemanol during the 1950s.
2 CONT
