1 NOTE {geni:about_me} [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sophie_de_Choiseul-Gouffier Sophie de Choiseul-Gouffier] (Lithuanian: Sofija Tyzenhauzaitė de Šuazel-Gufjė; 1790 – 28 May 1878) was a Lithuanian novelist. She was a member of the Lith
2 CONC uanian nobility from the Tyzenhaus family. She married Antoine Louis Octave de Choiseul-Gouffier, a French noble in service of Napoleon after the French invasion of Russia in 1812 and owner of Plateliai manor. She is one of the fi
2 CONC rst female writers in Lithuania. She wrote in French. Her novels are inspired by the life of females in contemporary Lithuanian nobility.
2 CONT
2 CONT ----
2 CONT
