1 NOTE {geni:about_me} I grew up with my mother's and her family's Russian past, their historical, cultural and spiritual roots. I  always felt emotionally very close to everything Russian.
2 CONT
2 CONT I had a very interesting career with the ICRC tracing missing people in and outside of Eastern Europe. During my frequent work related trips to Russia, I was able to visit the family graves in the Lavra Petcherskaia in Kiev, the S
2 CONC tandertskjoeld house on Vasilievskii ostrov (island of Vasilii) in St. Petersburg , the ancestor Nikolai Danilovitch in the Hermitage etc.
2 CONT
2 CONT My interests are in history, archeology, geneaology and music.
