2 TITL General Staff of the Rough Riders
2 NOTE It is interesting that Wheeler was appointed to head US Cavalry for the War in Cuba being, as he was, a former Confederate General.
2 NOTE It is interesting  that Leonard Wood had an extensive Arizona background as well:
3 CONT "In June 1885, Wood was contracted by the U.S. Army to act as an assistant surgeon without rank, and he was posted to the Department of Arizona.[15] In January 1886, Wood was nominated by the president for appointment in the U.S. 
3 CONC Army as assistant surgeon with the rank of first lieutenant.[16] His appointment was among several whose confirmation by the United States Senate was delayed until July 27, 1886.[17] Until that time, he continued as a contract sur
3 CONC geon and was stationed with the 4th Cavalry at Fort Huachuca, Arizona. Wood participated in the last campaign against Geronimo in the summer of 1886."
2 NOTE a better resolution of phot with complete captions: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Oswald_Brodie#/media/File:Theodore-roosevelt-and-officers.gif
2 NOTE It was Theodore Roosevelt who appointed Brodie to fill the vacancy of Governor of Arizona Territory
