2 CONT sorry but the Troubetzkoy spelling is with "ou" and not with "u" because it is the spelling until 1924 in Europe. After 1924, the spelling is changing to "Troubeyzkoï" and after WW II due to the change of phonetic it is "Trubetzko
2 CONC y". You can refer to "our Family's Album, a genealogical and photographic chronicle of the descendants of Nikolai Petrovitch Troubetzkoy". Fot the spelling of Wladimir, this is a familial particularity as well written on the Vital
2 CONC  Record! Sincerely,
2 CONT
