1 NOTE {geni:about_me} Served in the Revolutionary War Private, Captain Henry Jenne's company, Colonel John Hathaway's (2nd Bristol County) regiment; enlisted 8/2/1780; discharged 8/8/1780; service 6 days at Rhode Island on an alarm.  Ro
2 CONC ll dated Dartmouth.
2 CONT
2 CONT Was a successful in business for many years in New Bedford, MA.
2 CONT
2 CONT He was a Representative in 1809.
2 CONT
2 CONT He was a sea captain and ship owner.  He made at least one whaling voyage to the North Atlantic in 1821 returning 550 barrels of whale oil from the waters around the Cape Verde islands.
