1 OCCU Served in the Revolutionary War
1 TITL Captain
1 NOTE {geni:about_me} A Patriot of the American Revolution for MASSACHUSETTS with the rank of MAJOR.  [http://services.dar.org/public/dar_research/search_adb/?action=full&p_id=A085307  DAR Ancestor #  A085307]
2 CONT
2 CONT He served in the Revolutionary War, Rutland District (also given Barre) 2nd Lieutenant, Captian John Oliver's company, drafted from Colonel Nathan Sparhawk's regiment; list of officers appointeed to command men enllisted or drafte
2 CONC d from the Worchester County brigade, as returned to Major General Warren (year not given);  resident Turland District; company to join Colonel Hosiah Whitney's  or Colonel Nathan Sparhawk's regiment.  Also, 2d Lieutenant, Captain
2 CONC  John Black's (1st) company, Colonel Nathan Sparhawk's (7th Worcester County) regiment, list of officers, dated Petersham, 3/24/1776, chosen by the several companies in said regiment, as returned by Colonel Sparhawk and others, Fi
2 CONC eld Officers; residence Rutland District; ordered in Council 4/6/1776, that officers be commissioned; as reported commissioned 4/5/1776. also, Captain, 1st company, list of officers dated Barre, 5/5/1777, returned by Colonel Natha
2 CONC n Sparhawk as chosen in the 1st and 10th companies of the Worcester County regiment of MA militia; ordered in Council  5/14/1777, that said officers be commissioned; reported commissioned 5/14/1777.  Also Captain, Colonel Nathan S
2 CONC parhawk's regiment engaged 8/21/1777; discharged 8/25/1777; service ten days, including travel home (96 miles); residence Barre, company marched to reinforce army at Bennington under General Stark 8/21/1777; discharged 10/18/1777;
2 CONC  service 29 days, including travel home residence Barre; company marched under Major Jonas Wilder to reinforce the Northern army for 30 days.  Also, Captain, Colonel Nathan Sparhawk's regiment; pay roll made up for service of comp
2 CONC any from 9/17/1778, to 12/12/1778 at Dorchester.  Also, official record of a ballot by the House of Representatives, dated 1/30/1779, said Nye chosen 2nd Major, Colonel Jonathan Grout's 7th Worcester County regiment; appointment c
2 CONC oncurred by Council 1/30/1779; reported commissioned 1/30/1779.
