1 OCCU Served in the Revolutionary War
1 NOTE {geni:about_me} Patriot of the American Revolution for MASSACHUSETTS with the rank of SERGEANT.  [http://services.dar.org/Public/DAR_Research/search_adb/?action=full&p_id=A085399  DAR Ancestor # A085399]
2 CONT
2 CONT Served in the Revolutionary War
2 CONT * Corporal, Captain John Black's company, Colonel Jonathan Brewer's regiment; muster roll dated 8/1/1775; enlisted 4/20/1775; service three months thirteen days; residence Hutchinson (now Barre).
2 CONT * Served same company for eight months service in 1775, dated in camp Prospect Hill, 10/26/1775.
2 CONT * Petition signed by Nye, belonging to Captain Black's company, Colonel Brewers regiment asking for allowances for a great coat lost in battle.
2 CONT * Sergeant, Captain Ephraim Stockwell's company, Colonel Job Cushing's regiment; enlisted 7/28/1777, discharged 8/29/1777, company marched to Bennington to reinforce army under  General Stark.
2 CONT * Captain Benjamin Nye's company, enlisted 9/26/1777, discharged 10/18/1777, company marched under command of Major Jonas Wilder to reinforce Northern army for 30 days.
