1 NOTE {geni:about_me} https://personen.digitale-sammlungen.de//baltlex/Blatt_bsb00127527,00157.html?prozent=
2 CONT
2 CONT VI.
2 CONT
2 CONT
2 CONT ----
2 CONT [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Nieroth '''Carl Gustaf von Nieroth'''] (died 1712) was a Swedish officer and Governor-General of [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Estonia_under_Swedish_rule Swedish Estonia] 1709–1710 (though not 
2 CONC formally installed) and of Finland 1710–1712.
2 CONT
2 CONT '''The exact date and''' location of his birth are unknown, but believed to be in Finland. He was a son of the Baltic German Otto Nieroth and Gertrud Baranoff. 
2 CONT
2 CONT '''He was first recorded''' in 1671 as a cornet of the Swedish Army in [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swedish_Pomerania Swedish Pomerania]. He fought on different fronts in the Scanian War (1675-1679). During the winter of 1678-79
2 CONC  he headed a small garrison in northeastern Scania and was a leading figure in the small war against the local rebels, the snapphanar, who fought for Denmark.In this role, he was mentioned several times by Field Marshal Rutger von
2 CONC  Ascheberg.
2 CONT In 1692 he had risen to the rank of lieutenant colonel, in 1700 to major general and in 1704 to lieutenant general.
2 CONT
2 CONT '''During the''' [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Northern_War '''Great''' Northern War] Nieroth was involved in several successful battles, the [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Warsaw_(1705 Battle of Warsaw] (1705) be
2 CONC ing his greatest success.
2 CONT
2 CONT '''After''' [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siege_of_Viborg_(1710 '''Viipuri was lost'''] in 1710, Nieroth was sent to try to reclaim it. He assembled 10,000 men, who besieged the city in 1711 but lacked equipment to enter it, and 
2 CONC had to retreat. 
2 CONT
2 CONT '''He died suddenly''' during a temporary halt in Sarvlax manor (Finnish: Sarvilahti) in Pernå parish, on 25 January 1712.
2 CONT
2 CONT '''He was married''' on 7 January 1686 in Stockholm to '''Christina Margareta Horn''' (d. 17 September 1703).
2 CONT
2 CONT '''He was elevated''' to baron, then count on 26 June 1706.
2 CONT
2 CONT /////
2 CONT
2 CONT [https://www.adelsvapen.com/genealogi/Nieroth_nr_52 '''Carl Nieroth''', natural., friherre och '''greve Nieroth, till Djulfors'''] i St. Malms socken Södermanlands län. 
2 CONT
2 CONT '''Född omkr. 1650'''. Kornett vid W. Wrangels regemente i Pommern 1673. Löjtnant därst. 1675. Kapten vid Brunows finska regemente 1677. Ryttmästare vid livregementet till häst s. å. Löjtnant vid drabanterna 1679. Överstelöjtnant 
2 CONC vid södra skånska kavalleriregementet 1692. 
2 CONT
2 CONT '''Natural. svensk''' adelsman 1693, introd. s. å. på adliga ättens von Nieroths, n:o 564 (dåvar. n:o 529). 
2 CONT
2 CONT '''Överstelöjtnant vid''' livdrabanterna 1695. Generalmajor av kavalleriet samt överste för Smålands kavalleriregemente 1700. Generallöjtnant av kavalleriet 1704. 
2 CONT
2 CONT '''K. råd samt''' president i Göta hovrätt 1705. 
2 CONT
2 CONT '''Friherre och''' greve 1706 (sonen 1719 såsom greve introd. under n:o 52). 
2 CONT
2 CONT '''Generalguvernör i''' Estland 1709. Avsked från presidentsskapet i Göta hovrätt 1710. General ''en chef'' i Finland s. å. 
2 CONT
2 CONT '''Död 1712'''-01-25 Sarvlaks. 
2 CONT
2 CONT  "Han var en tapper krigare och skicklig anförare. Slog bland annat den 20 Juli 1704 vid Warschau 4,000 sachsare och 6,000 polacker under general Paijkulls befäl samt tog denne med många flera tillfånga, varigenom Sveriges samt ko
2 CONC nung Stanislai bästa i verklig mån befordrades. Under sitt kommando i Finland slutligen uppehöll han efter Wiborgs övergång ryska armén i två år, så att den ej kunde infalla i landet." 
2 CONT
2 CONT '''Gift 1686-01-07''' i Stockholm med friherrinnan [https://www.adelsvapen.com/genealogi/Horn_af_Marienborg_nr_21#TAB_3 Christina Margareta Horn af Marienborg], död 1703-09-19 Brevik och begraven i Botkyrka kyrka, Stockholms län, 
2 CONC dotter av riksrådet, fältmarskalken och generalguvernören Henrik Henriksson Horn af Kanckas, och hans 3:e fru [https://www.adelsvapen.com/genealogi/Ribbing_nr_15#TAB_71 Emerentia Ribbing].
2 CONT <br/>
2 CONT <br/>
