1 NOTE {geni:about_me} Paternal haplogroup I-M438, I-S17250.  Maternal haplogroup is J1c3.
2 CONT
2 CONT Origin and Migrations of Haplogroups I-M438   The men of haplogroup I-M438 radiated outward from the Balkans into the eastern half of the continent. Their descendants are found most concentrated in eastern Europe and western Russi
2 CONC a, where they make up 40% of the male population in Bosnia and 30% in Croatia. Some, however, moved farther north and west. Nearly 40% of men on the Mediterranean island of Sardinia carry haplogroup I-M438, and they are also relat
2 CONC ively common in the Netherlands and Germany. Finally, they can also be found in Sweden, particularly in the northern province of Vasterbotten, where their ancestors likely arrived with the more recent migration of German and Dutch
2 CONC  immigrants during the 17th century.
2 CONT
2 CONT Today, J1c3 is found almost exclusively within Europe, and researchers speculate that the traces of J1c3 in the Middle East are due to eastward migrations of people much later in human history.
