1 NOTE {geni:about_me} Born in Liverpool, England, to Boris Fulda and Catherine Von Dehn, Michael also lived in Switzerland and Argentina before moving to the United States in 1962 and becoming a citizen in 1966. Michael held masters and
2 CONC  doctoral degrees in International Studies from American University in Washington, DC. He was a veteran of the US Army and Army Reserves. Michael was a retired professor of Political Science and Ballroom Dance at the Fairmont Stat
2 CONC e College. In the 1980s, he served as the WV State Committee Chairman for John Anderson’s presidential run. He was a visiting lecturer at Bauman University in Moscow, Russia, a director of the National Space Society, and the presi
2 CONC dent of the Institute for the Social Science Study of Space.
2 CONT
2 CONT Michael was a lifelong lover and supporter of the arts. He served on the Board of Directors of the Fairmont Chamber Music Society, was the founder and faculty advisor of the Dancing Falcons ballroom dancing club, and a passionate 
2 CONC supporter of PBS. In addition to the arts, Michael valued the importance of Boy Scouting. He, himself was a 2nd generation scout and member of the Advancement Committee of his local Boy Scout District.
